data.meta_description: Download Images of  - Free for commercial use, no attribution required. From: The Fuller farmhouse on the road to West Barnstable was built about 1800. The south wing was added in 1892, to Opposite the Mecarta house was the summer home of the famous musician Felix Winternitz, with a boathouse at Warren's Cove. In 1929, it was bought by the wife of the famous writer J. P. Marquand (1893-1960). The house burned down on Halloween 1971. Find  images dated from 1800 to 2020.
